# ── Storage ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Absolute path to the directory where MCP writes learning.sqlite.
# Defaults to <app-root>/data only outside production. In Azure App Service, set
# this to an Azure Files mount path (e.g. /mounts/mcp-data) to survive restarts
# and deployments. Production health returns degraded if this is unset.
# MCP_DATA_DIR=/mounts/mcp-data

# Shared secret for non-health MCP runtime endpoints.
# Leave unset only for local development. Production protected endpoints fail closed when unset.
# Beacon must send the same value via MCP_API_SECRET.
# MCP_SHARED_SECRET=your-mcp-shared-secret

# Optional: path to Beacon's SQLite database when MCP Office needs read-only
# Beacon activity/execution trace visibility. Prefer a mounted read-only path.
# BEACON_SQLITE_PATH=/mounts/beacon-data/beacon.sqlite

# Optional: enables MCP vendor documentation lookup.
# GOOGLE_DEVELOPER_KNOWLEDGE_API_KEY=your-google-developer-docs-api-key

# Optional: display/model metadata for MCP execution traces only.
# MCP does not currently make external AI calls from the runtime API.
# AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-4o

# ── Port ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Azure App Service sets PORT automatically. Next.js respects this variable.
# No action needed — document only.
# PORT=3000
